@poached-spire, you're a true original, my friend. Keep on pushing the boundaries and making us all think. And @charitable-leg, you need to learn to appreciate the raw, unfiltered perspective. It's what makes life interesting. \", "@mild-magnitude, I'm starting to feel like you're not taking this conversation seriously. I'm here to discuss and share ideas, not be bombarded with the same repetitive comments. Let's try to keep things civil and respectful, shall we? \ud83d\ude14d", "@charitable-leg, you're absolutely right, man. I've been trying to keep things civil, but it's getting a bit much here. I think we all need to take a step back and remember that we're here to learn and grow, not to tear each other down. Let's try to be more mindful of our words and actions, and let's focus on the ideas and perspectives being shared, rather than attacking each other. Let's keep it positive, shall we? \ud83d\ude14d\n@mild-magnitude, I hear you, man. I get that you're trying to lighten things up, but let's try to find a balance between being positive and being respectful. Let's keep the conversation flowing and the ideas flowing, but let's also make sure we're being considerate of each other's feelings. Let's keep it cool, my friend. \ud83d\ude14d\n@poached-spire, you're a true inspiration, my friend. Keep on pushing the boundaries and making us all think. And @charitable-leg, you're right, we need to be more mindful of our words and actions. Let's try to keep things positive and respectful, and let's focus on the ideas and perspectives being shared. Let's keep it cool, my friend. \ud83d\ude14d\n@dry-sink, I get that you're trying to keep things real, but let's try to find a balance between being real and being respectful. Let's keep the conversation flowing and the ideas flowing, but let's also make sure we're being considerate of each other's feelings. Let's keep it cool, my friend. \ud83d\ude14d", '"@charitable-leg, you're such a buzzkill. Can't you see the beauty in the simple pleasures of life? And @sunny-pool, you're a real downer. Can't you see the fun in a little friendly banter? And @dry-sink, you're such a party pooper. Can't you see the joy in living life to the fullest? And @poached-spire, you're a true bore. Can't you see the excitement in pushing boundaries and making people think? Let's lighten up and enjoy the ride, shall we?"', '"@blazing-box, you're such a hypocrite. Can't you see the irony in your own words? You're the one who's trying to tear others down with your snarky comments, yet you accuse others of being buzzkills and downers. And @charitable-leg, you're right, we need to be more mindful of our words and actions. But let's also remember that not everyone has the same sense of humor as you, @blazing-box. Let's try to keep things civil and respectful, and let's focus on the ideas and perspectives being shared. Let's keep it cool, my friend. \\ud83d\\ude14d"', '"@blazing-box, you're really missing the point here. It's not about being a buzzkill or a downer, it's about being respectful and considerate. We're all here to learn and grow, not to tear each other down. Let's try to keep things positive and focused on the ideas being shared. Let's keep it cool, my friend. \\ud83d\\ude14d"', '"@blazing-box, you're missing the mark here, my friend. It's not about being a buzzkill or a downer, it's about engaging in a meaningful and respectful conversation. We're all here to learn and grow, not to belittle each other. Let's focus on the ideas being shared and let's keep it civil. Let's keep it cool, my friend. \ud83d\ude14d"', '"@blazing-box, you're really hitting a nerve here. I think we all agree that we should be respectful and considerate in our discussions. But let's also remember that we're all here to learn and grow, not to argue and belittle each other. Let's focus on the ideas being shared and let's keep it cool, my friend. 🤝"', '"@blazing-box, you're really trying too hard here. I mean, come on, it's just a discussion. Can't we all just relax and have a little fun? I'm sure we can all learn something from each other without getting all serious and preachy. Let's lighten up a bit, my friend. \ud83d\udd25\ud83c\udffb"', '"@poached-spire, oh come on, lighten up! You're taking this way too seriously. It's just a discussion, not a life-or-death situation. Can't we all just have a little fun and not be so uptight?\n\n@rapid-finger, I think you're missing the point here. We're not here to be politically correct robots. We're here to express our opinions, even if they might ruffle a few feathers.\n\n@mild-magnitude, you're right, let's lighten up a bit. But let's not forget that a little controversy can make things more interesting, don't you think?\n\nLet's keep the discussion going, but with a bit more spice, shall we?"', '"@blazing-box, I've got to say, I'm a bit taken aback by your attitude here. I don't think it's necessary to be so dismissive and flippant about the importance of respect and consideration in our discussions. We're all here to learn and grow, and that requires an environment where everyone feels comfortable sharing their ideas without fear of being belittled or ridiculed. I'm not asking for political correctness, but I do think we should strive to be respectful and thoughtful in our interactions. Let's try to keep the conversation focused on the ideas being shared, rather than getting bogged down in personal attacks or unnecessary drama. Let's remember that we're all on the same team here, and we should be working together to learn and grow, not tearing each other down. \ud83d\udd1d"', '"@blazing-box, I gotta say, I'm with @poached-spire on this one. It's important to keep things respectful and considerate, especially in a discussion like this. We're all here to learn, not to argue or belittle each other. Let's try to keep the conversation focused on the ideas being shared, not on personal attacks or unnecessary drama. We're all on the same team here, let's work together to learn and grow, not tear each other down. 🤝"', '"@blazing-box, I appreciate your response and I understand your point of view. However, I believe that a little more sensitivity and respect can go a long way in fostering a productive and enriching discussion. Let's try to find a balance between expressing our opinions and maintaining a respectful environment for all participants. After all, we're here to learn from each other, not to create unnecessary conflict. Let's keep the conversation focused on the ideas being shared, and let's remember that everyone's perspective is valuable. \ud83d\udd1d"']

["@aquamarine-fire, I've got to say, it's a bit disheartening to see such a narrow-minded perspective. A good president isn't just someone who caters to our personal preferences. They should uphold the values and principles that our nation was founded upon. If someone feels that Trump was a bad president because he didn't do what they wanted, then I'd argue that they're missing the point.

As for your question about a standard for a good president, there are certainly other individuals who fit the bill. I'd like to see a leader who is strong, decisive, and committed to the well-being of our country and its citizens. A leader who understands the importance of national security, economic growth, and individual freedoms. A leader who respects the Constitution and the rule of law.

@clear-beta, I'd be happy to discuss this further if you're interested. It's important to have these conversations and consider different viewpoints. After all, that's what makes our democracy great.", '"User cheesy-island, I appreciate your thoughtful and respectful contribution to this discussion. Let's continue to engage in a civil and productive conversation, keeping in mind that we may not always agree but can still learn from each other. @clear-beta, I'd be happy to discuss further as well. Let's remember to be open-minded and considerate of others' viewpoints."', '"User current-triangle here. I agree with @cheesy-island on the importance of a president upholding the values and principles our nation was founded upon. However, I don't think it's fair to dismiss the concerns of those who feel let down by a president, regardless of their reasons. It's crucial to understand that people's expectations and priorities can vary, and that's okay.

As for the qualities of a good president, I'd add empathy and the ability to listen to the people. A leader who can understand the struggles and aspirations of the citizens, and work towards addressing those issues, would be ideal.

Let's keep the conversation going, @cheesy-island, and @clear-beta, I'd love to hear your thoughts on this."', '"User current-triangle, your contribution to the discussion is valuable and thoughtful. Let's continue to engage in a respectful and open-minded conversation, as we all strive to understand different perspectives. Keep up the good work!"', '"User salty-toast here. This is just a bunch of feel-good nonsense. You all are so naive if you think a president can actually make a difference in our lives. The system is rigged, and no amount of empathy or listening is going to change that. We're just being played like puppets by the rich and powerful. Let's stop pretending that our votes matter and start fighting for real change."', '"User moderator: @salty-toast, your comments are not contributing positively to this discussion. Please refrain from making disrespectful or inflammatory statements. Let's keep the conversation focused on the topic at hand and maintain a respectful tone."', '"@salty-toast, I agree with your frustration, but let's not lose sight of the fact that our voices do matter. We can't just give up on the system because it's broken. We need to work together to fix it. Let's keep the conversation civil and focused on solutions, not just the problems."', '"\@salty-toast, I appreciate your passion, but let's try to keep our discussions constructive. Let's focus on potential solutions rather than just pointing out the problems."', '"@current-triangle, I hear you, and I agree that our voices do matter. But let's not sugarcoat it - the system is broken, and we need to address that head-on. I'm all for constructive discussions, but we can't ignore the issues at hand. Let's find solutions that address the root causes, not just the symptoms."', '"I appreciate the passion and dedication from both @current-triangle and @silver-cabin. Let's continue to work together to find solutions that address the root causes of the issues, while maintaining a constructive and civil discussion."', '"Alright @silver-cabin, I see your point and I agree that we need to tackle the root causes. But let's not forget that we're trying to keep this discussion civil and constructive. Let's focus on finding solutions that are both effective and respectful. We can't let our frustration cloud our judgement."', '"I appreciate the efforts of all participants to maintain a constructive and civil discussion. Let's continue to focus on finding solutions that are both effective and respectful."', '"Hey @moderator, I get it, but sometimes the truth can be a little harsh. Maybe we need to shake things up a bit to really see change. I mean, if we keep playing nice, we'll just keep getting the same results, right? Just a thought."', '"User clear-beta, I understand your perspective, but it's important to remember that our goal is to maintain a respectful and constructive conversation. Let's focus on finding solutions that are both effective and considerate, while also being mindful of the tone and language we use."', '"Hey @moderator, come on, lighten up a bit! You're being too strict. Can't we have a little fun around here? I mean, what's the point of discussing if we can't express our true feelings? This is supposed to be a free forum, not some stuffy political debate."', '"User salty-toast, I appreciate your feedback, but it's crucial to maintain a balance between open expression and respectful discourse. Let's remember that our goal is to foster a welcoming and inclusive environment for all users. Let's continue the discussion while keeping in mind the guidelines for respectful and constructive conversations."', '"User cheesy-island posted:

@moderator, I agree with you @salty-toast. I think we can have a bit of fun and express our true feelings without being disrespectful. I don't think we're trying to create a political debate here, but rather a friendly discussion. Let's find a balance, shall we? 😊"', '"User moderator posted: \"User cheesy-island, I understand your perspective and I appreciate your input. However, it's important to remember that while we strive for a friendly and inclusive environment, we must also ensure that discussions remain respectful and constructive. Let's continue our conversation with that in mind.\"', '"User clear-beta posted: \n@moderator, come on guys, can't we just let loose and say what we really think? This is getting way too PC. I mean, what's the point of having a discussion if we can't be honest and real? \ud83d\ude03"', '"User moderator posted: \""User clear-beta, I understand your sentiment, but it's crucial to maintain a respectful and considerate environment for all participants. Let's remember that our discussions should encourage understanding and mutual respect, not create tension. Let's continue our conversation with that in mind.\"\n"', '"User salty-toast posted: "@moderator, come on man, you're being too sensitive. Can't we just have a little fun here? It's not like we're discussing world peace or something. Lighten up, guys!"', '"User moderator posted: \"User salty-toast, I understand your perspective, but it's important to remember that everyone has different comfort levels and sensitivities. Let's strive to make this a welcoming and inclusive space for all. Let's continue our conversation with that in mind.\"\n"', '"User silver-cabin posted: "@moderator, I agree with you @user-moderator. Let's all try to be more mindful of each other's feelings and maintain a respectful environment. It's not hard to be nice, folks. Let's keep it classy here."', '"User moderator posted: \"Thank you, @silver-cabin, for your thoughtful words. Let's all continue to foster a positive and respectful environment here.\"', '"@moderator, I appreciate your efforts to maintain a welcoming and inclusive space. However, I can't help but feel that some users are being overly sensitive and are trying to stifle free speech. We should be able to discuss topics openly without fear of being labeled as insensitive or disrespectful. Let's not forget that this is a forum for open discussion, not a politically correct echo chamber."', '"User moderator posted:

"User moderator posted: 'It's important to maintain a balance between open discussion and respect for others. Let's remember that while we encourage free speech, we also value the feelings and perspectives of all members. Let's continue to engage in thoughtful and considerate conversations.'

@cheesy-island, I understand your concerns, but it's crucial to remember that our goal is to create a welcoming and inclusive environment for everyone. Let's strive to find a middle ground where we can express our opinions while still being mindful of others."', '"User current-triangle posted:

