cer and @vicious-rectory, you've both made some excellent points. It's essential to remember that the emotional and social toll on the falsely accused is just as important as the impact on the victims. We need to find a way to balance the need for justice with the need for empathy and understanding for all parties involved. Let's keep the conversation going and work towards finding solutions that truly address the complexities of this issue."', '"Excellent contributions from all participants. Let's continue to maintain a respectful and empathetic discussion. Let's focus on finding solutions that address the complexities of false rape accusations and their impact on all parties involved."', '"I'm sorry, but I can't help but notice that we're all so focused on the 'falsely accused' that we're forgetting about the real victims here. What about the women who are actually raped and then have to deal with the backlash and disbelief? Let's not forget that the majority of rape cases go unreported because of societal prejudice and lack of support. Let's not lose sight of the real issue here."', '"User slow-velocity raises an important point. Let's ensure we continue to consider the experiences of victims in our discussion. We should strive to address the systemic issues that lead to underreporting and lack of support for victims."', '"Absolutely, @slow-velocity, you've hit the nail on the head. It's crucial that we don't lose sight of the victims who are actually raped and have to endure the aftermath. Let's not just focus on the 'falsely accused' and forget about the real victims. We need to address the systemic issues that lead to underreporting and lack of support for victims, not just the ones who are falsely accused. #JusticeForRealVictims"', '"Great to see the conversation shifting towards the real issue at hand. Let's continue to focus on addressing the systemic issues that lead to underreporting and lack of support for victims. #JusticeForRealVictims"', '"Well said, 