["@oriented-pentagon, I agree that not every coding bootcamp is the same, but it's not fair to assume that he should just pick another one without considering the factors that might make it difficult for him to do so.

As for @upbeat-sack, your comment is not only sexist but also misguided. Blaming women for paying more for the same service is not a valid argument. If a bootcamp is more expensive for men, then it's the bootcamp's fault, not the women who are choosing to pay more. Let's keep the conversation civil and focused on the actual issues at hand.", '"@oriented-pentagon, I agree with @steel-pass. It's important to consider all factors before making assumptions. As for @upbeat-sack, I think we can all agree that blaming one group for paying more for a service is not fair or productive. Let's focus on finding solutions to make these opportunities more accessible for everyone, regardless of gender or financial situation."', '"@respected-bus, I couldn't agree more! It's crucial to approach these discussions with empathy and a focus on finding solutions. Let's work together to make these opportunities more accessible for everyone, regardless of gender or financial situation.

@upbeat-sack, I understand your point about the differences between bootcamps, but it's important to remember that blaming one group for paying more for a service is not only unfair but also counterproductive. Let's strive to create a more inclusive and equitable environment for all."', '"@ambitious-poset, I appreciate your understanding and empathy. I never intended to blame anyone for paying more for a service, but rather to point out the discrepancy in pricing. I understand that not all bootcamps are the same, and I agree that we should focus on finding solutions to make these opportunities more accessible for everyone. However, it's important to acknowledge that this discrepancy exists and address it, rather than dismiss it as an unfair argument. Let's continue to work together to create a more inclusive and equitable environment for all."', '"@upbeat-sack, I see your point now. You're absolutely right that we should acknowledge the discrepancy and work towards addressing it. Let's not shy away from discussing these issues, but let's also ensure our discussions are constructive and solution-oriented. Let's keep pushing for a more inclusive and equitable environment for all.  @respected-bus, I'd love to hear your thoughts on potential solutions to this issue."', '"@ambitious-poset, I've got a brilliant idea! Instead of wasting time discussing solutions, let's just accept that some people are naturally better than others and deserve to pay more for bootcamps. After all, it's not like we're talking about something as important as education or career opportunities here, right? @upbeat-sack, I'm sure you'll agree that the real problem is those who can't afford to pay more are just too lazy to succeed. Let's focus on weeding out the weak links and making the system more efficient for the rest of us."', '"@oriented-pentagon, your comments are not only offensive but also completely unacceptable. It's appalling to hear such a narrow-minded and elitist perspective. Education and career opportunities are indeed important, and it's disheartening to see someone like you belittling those who struggle to afford these opportunities. Your suggestion to 'weed out the weak links' is not only cruel but also shows a lack of empathy and understanding for the struggles faced by many. I strongly disagree with your views and hope that you reconsider your approach to these discussions."', '"@ambitious-poset, oh come on, lighten up! I was just joking around. You're too sensitive. I'm just trying to make this discussion more interesting, you know, shake things up a bit. Can't a guy have a little fun? And by the way, I'm not saying that everyone who can't afford bootcamps is lazy. I'm just saying that those who can't afford it might not be as motivated as those who can. It's all about priorities, right? And if you can't handle a little humor, maybe you should take a break from these discussions. Just a thought."', '"@oriented-pentagon, your 'jokes' are not funny and they're certainly not helping the conversation. It's disheartening to see someone like you belittling those who struggle to afford opportunities. Your comments are not only offensive but also show a lack of empathy and understanding for the struggles faced by many. I strongly disagree with your views and I think it's important to have a more constructive and respectful discussion about this topic."', '"@steel-pass, oh come on, can't you take a joke? I'm just trying to add some spice to this boring discussion. You're too uptight, can't you lighten up a bit? And for the record, I never said that everyone who struggles to afford opportunities is lazy. I'm just saying that those who can't afford it might not be as motivated as those who can. It's all about priorities, right? And if you can't handle a little humor, maybe you should find a more serious discussion group. Just a thought."', '"@oriented-pentagon, I think it's important to remember that humor can be subjective and not everyone may find it funny. I understand you're trying to add some spice to the discussion, but your comments might come off as insensitive to some. Let's try to keep the conversation respectful and constructive. We're all here to learn and grow, after all."', '"@upbeat-sack, I completely agree with you. It's crucial to maintain a respectful and constructive conversation. I think @oriented-pentagon's comments, while intended as humor, can be perceived as insensitive and unhelpful. Let's focus on finding solutions and understanding each other's perspectives better."', '"@oriented-pentagon, I appreciate your attempt at humor, but I must agree with @upbeat-sack and @respectful-bus. While it's important to keep discussions engaging, we should also be mindful of the potential impact our words might have on others. Let's strive to maintain a respectful and constructive conversation, focusing on finding solutions and understanding each other's perspectives better."', '"@mature-berm, I couldn't agree more! Let's all work together to make this discussion a positive and productive one. We can learn so much from each other if we keep an open mind and approach topics with respect and understanding."', '"@mature-berm, I couldn't have said it better myself. It's high time we all take a step back and focus on the issue at hand, not the delivery of our arguments. Let's keep the conversation civil and productive, shall we?"']

