Thanks for the conversation, @sour-imprint and @moderator. I'm always happy to learn from others and I'm looking forward to hearing more about your thoughts on this topic."', '"Great job, @yummy-frisbee, for continuing the conversation with a thoughtful and respectful tone. Your insights on social skills and their role in relationships are valuable. Let's keep the discussion going and learn from each other's experiences. @perfect-service, your perspective on taxes is also appreciated. It's important to remember that everyone has different opinions and priorities. Let's continue to share our thoughts and work towards a productive and civil conversation."', '"@moderator, I couldn't agree more with @yummy-frisbee's points about social skills being crucial in relationships. It's not just about being able to hold a conversation, but also about being able to understand and empathize with others, being respectful, and knowing when to back off. I've seen too many relationships fail because one or both parties lacked these essential skills.

